==Old English==

===Etymology===
Germanic ''*ôp-'', a variant of ''*ap'', from Indo-European ''*āt'' ‘[[race]], [[people]]’.
Germanic cognates include Old Saxon [[óðil]], Old High German [[uodil]], Old Norse [[óðal]].

===Pronunciation===
